00:16:46,465 --> 00:16:47,985
Maybe you haven't met the right man.

246
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:51,111
It's a small village, Gaston.
I've met them all.

247
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:54,672
Well, maybe you should take
another look.

248
00:16:55,010 --> 00:16:56,563
Some of us have changed.

249
00:16:56,986 --> 00:16:57,986
Gaston,

250
00:16:58,104 --> 00:17:00,037
we could never make each other happy.

251
00:17:00,385 --> 00:17:02,935
No one can changed that much.

252
00:17:03,311 --> 00:17:04,368
Oh, Belle.

253
00:17:05,732 --> 00:17:09,033
Do you know what happens to spinsters in this village
after their fathers died?

254
00:17:09,246 --> 00:17:10,968
Coins? Could you spare me coins?

255
00:17:11,234 --> 00:17:13,893
They beg for scraps,
like poor Agathe.

256
00:17:14,213 --> 00:17:16,711
This is our world, Belle.

257
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:19,869
For simple folk like us,
it doesn't getting better.

258
00:17:20,256 --> 00:17:21,925
I want to be a farm girl.

259
00:17:22,189 --> 00:17:24,385
But I'm not simple.
And..

260
00:17:24,714 --> 00:17:28,385
I'm never going to marry you, Gaston.

261
00:17:28,641 --> 00:17:29,641
I'm sorry!

262
00:17:46,103 --> 00:17:47,388
<i>Can you imagine?</i>

263
00:17:47,719 --> 00:17:50,518
<i>Me? The wife of that boorish,</i>

264
00:17:50,787 --> 00:17:51,787
<i>brainless...</i>

265
00:17:52,543 --> 00:17:56,131
<i>Madam Gaston, can't you just see it?</i>

266
00:17:56,469 --> 00:18:00,137
<i>Madame Gaston, his little wife. Ugh!</i>

267
00:18:00,249 --> 00:18:03,311
<i>No, Sir. Not me, I guarantee it</i>

268
00:18:03,631 --> 00:18:07,389
<i>I want much more than this
provincial life</i>

269
00:18:17,842 --> 00:18:22,777
<i>I want adventure in the great wide
somewhere</i>

270
00:18:23,813 --> 00:18:27,743
<i>I want it more than I can tell</i>

271
00:18:28,922 --> 00:18:32,832
<i>And for once it might be grand</i>

272
00:18:33,843 --> 00:18:37,555
<i>To have someone understand</i>

273
00:18:39,025 --> 00:18:44,852
I want so much more than they've got planned

274
00:18:59,063 --> 00:19:00,063
The woods are lovely.

275
00:19:00,427 --> 00:19:02,823
I only wish I'd recognized them.

276
00:19:03,247 --> 00:19:06,226
You know where we are, Philippe?
Cause I don't.

277
00:19:11,448 --> 00:19:14,136
It's all right. It's all right. Philippe.

278
00:19:18,698 --> 00:19:19,917
Yes, we can go this way.

279
00:19:21,010 --> 00:19:22,664
Go on. To the right.

280
00:19:23,610 --> 00:19:25,557
That's it!

281
00:19:25,890 --> 00:19:27,175
Come on!

282
00:19:27,717 --> 00:19:28,717
One door closes,

283
00:19:28,882 --> 00:19:29,989
another one opens.

284
00:19:31,987 --> 00:19:34,131
All right, boy.
Just a bit of snow.

285
00:19:34,668 --> 00:19:36,081
In June.

286
00:19:37,257 --> 00:19:38,297
Mind your step.

287
00:19:38,788 --> 00:19:40,348
It's slippery.

288
00:19:51,675 --> 00:19:53,616
Go, go Philippe! Come on!

289
00:20:01,894 --> 00:20:03,183
Come on!

290
00:20:03,935 --> 00:20:05,557
Go, Philippe! Go!

291
00:20:38,340 --> 00:20:39,612
Philippe!

292
00:20:41,302 --> 00:20:42,581
Good boy.

293
00:20:44,941 --> 00:20:46,842
Go, boy! Go!

294
00:21:00,103 --> 00:21:02,047
Philippe, you saved my life!

295
00:21:03,204 --> 00:21:04,814
Well done. Ehh.

296
00:21:06,468 --> 00:21:10,024
They'll have to get their dinner
somewhere else, won't they?

297
00:21:17,683 --> 00:21:18,753
Look!

298
00:21:19,071 --> 00:21:20,146
It's hay!

299
00:21:20,901 --> 00:21:21,901
And water.

300
00:21:22,113 --> 00:21:24,588
You are safe, my old friend.

301
00:21:25,671 --> 00:21:29,830
I'll go pay my respects to our
unwitting host.

302
00:21:30,642 --> 00:21:32,848
Whoever that may be.

303
00:22:07,278 --> 00:22:08,519
Thank you.

304
00:22:09,353 --> 00:22:10,473
Thank...

305
00:22:17,293 --> 00:22:18,293
Hello?

306
00:22:21,034 --> 00:22:22,034
Hello?

307
00:22:22,394 --> 00:22:24,085
Sorry to intrude.

308
00:22:24,294 --> 00:22:26,189
I'm a.. just a traveler,

309
00:22:26,956 --> 00:22:29,213
seeking shelter from the storm.

310
00:22:31,106 --> 00:22:32,975
Sorry to disturb you.

311
00:22:38,516 --> 00:22:39,826
Anyone home?

312
00:22:40,141 --> 00:22:41,488
Anyone awake?

313
00:22:44,238 --> 00:22:45,824
He must''ve lost his way
in the woods.

314
00:22:46,125 --> 00:22:47,958
You have to keep quite!

315
00:22:49,878 --> 00:22:51,181
Excuse me?

316
00:22:55,443 --> 00:22:57,085
Beautiful.

317
00:23:02,625 --> 00:23:04,261
Extraordinary.

318
00:23:13,961 --> 00:23:15,068
A man of taste.

319
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:16,778
He was talking about me.

320
00:23:32,788 --> 00:23:35,659
Well, wherever you are..

321
00:23:36,764 --> 00:23:40,182
I'm just going to warm myself
by the fire.

322
00:23:47,766 --> 00:23:49,032
That's better.

323
00:23:50,896 --> 00:23:51,926
Oh, much better.

324
00:24:10,343 --> 00:24:11,709
Thank you.

325
00:24:25,872 --> 00:24:28,432
Mom said I wasn't supposed to move,
because it might be scary.

326
00:24:30,070 --> 00:24:31,327
Sorry.

327
00:24:35,893 --> 00:24:37,320
It's alright.

328
00:24:44,628 --> 00:24:45,628
I cannot..

329
00:24:46,128 --> 00:24:49,693
Thank you enough for your hospitality.

330
00:24:50,475 --> 00:24:51,716
I'll..

331
00:24:53,559 --> 00:24:56,339
leave you..

332
00:24:58,175 --> 00:25:00,014
and good night.

333
00:25:00,375 --> 00:25:02,775
Come on Philippe, go! Go!

334
00:25:05,726 --> 00:25:07,477
No, wait, wait, wait!

335
00:25:07,771 --> 00:25:09,476
Roses. I nearly forgot.

336
00:25:10,409 --> 00:25:12,068
Stay here.

337
00:25:13,022 --> 00:25:14,699
I promised Belle a rose.

338
00:25:38,980 --> 00:25:39,980
There!

339
00:26:17,295 --> 00:26:18,295
Philippe!

340
00:26:24,487 --> 00:26:25,487
What happened?

341
00:26:26,938 --> 00:26:28,102
Where is Papa?

342
00:26:28,773 --> 00:26:29,773
Take me to him!

343
00:27:22,284 --> 00:27:23,879
Look! Cogsworth!

344
00:27:24,460 --> 00:27:25,749
A beautiful girl!

345
00:27:25,994 --> 00:27:28,253
Yes! I can see it's a girl.

346
00:27:28,760 --> 00:27:30,196
I lost my hands, but my eyes.

347
00:27:30,536 --> 00:27:31,921
But, what if she's the one?

348
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:33,695
The one who'll break the spell?

349
00:27:34,797 --> 00:27:35,797
Who said that?

350
00:27:37,222 --> 00:27:38,222
Who's there?

351
00:28:13,002 --> 00:28:14,057
Papa?

352
00:28:21,197 --> 00:28:22,642
Papa, is that you?

353
00:28:23,046 --> 00:28:24,046
Belle!

354
00:28:24,304 --> 00:28:25,735
How did you find me?

355
00:28:26,129 --> 00:28:27,559
Your hands are iced.

356
00:28:27,959 --> 00:28:29,079
We need to get you home.

357
00:28:29,289 --> 00:28:31,044
Belle, now you must leave!

358
00:28:31,325 --> 00:28:33,670
This castle is alive!

359
00:28:34,029 --> 00:28:35,669
Now, go before he finds you!

360
00:28:35,889 --> 00:28:36,889
Who?

361
00:28:45,926 --> 00:28:47,427
Who's there?

362
00:28:48,406 --> 00:28:49,605
Who are you?

363
00:28:49,989 --> 00:28:51,618
Who are you?

364
00:28:52,005 --> 00:28:53,962
I've come to my father.

365
00:28:54,661 --> 00:28:57,515
Your father is a thief!

366
00:28:57,836 --> 00:28:58,976
Liar!

367
00:28:59,246 --> 00:29:00,479
He stole a rose.

368
00:29:00,928 --> 00:29:02,211
I asked the rose.

369
00:29:02,508 --> 00:29:03,798
Punish me, not him!

370
00:29:04,084 --> 00:29:05,084
No!

371
00:29:05,109 --> 00:29:06,109
He means forever!

372
00:29:07,509 --> 00:29:11,409
Apparently, that's what happens around here
when you pick a flower!

373
00:29:13,208 --> 00:29:15,203
A life sentence for a rose?

374
00:29:17,895 --> 00:29:20,294
I received eternal damnation for one.

375
00:29:20,530 --> 00:29:22,621
I merely locking him away.

376
00:29:23,511 --> 00:29:26,530
Do you choose to take you father's
place?

377
00:29:27,851 --> 00:29:28,911
Come in to the light.

378
00:29:37,933 --> 00:29:38,933
Choose.

379
00:29:39,197 --> 00:29:41,252
Belle, I won't let you do this.

380
00:29:41,579 --> 00:29:42,854
I lost your mother.

381
00:29:43,235 --> 00:29:45,414
I won't lose you, too!

382
00:29:46,014 --> 00:29:47,065
Now, go!

383
00:29:47,379 --> 00:29:48,749
Go!

384
00:29:50,212 --> 00:29:52,300
All right, Papa. I'll leave.

385
00:29:55,660 --> 00:29:57,260
I need a minute alone with him.

386
00:29:58,936 --> 00:29:59,966
You are so cruel,

387
00:30:00,226 --> 00:30:02,822
did you won't allow a daughter
to say her father goodbye?

388
00:30:05,226 --> 00:30:07,429
Forever can spare a minute.

389
00:30:26,355 --> 00:30:30,497
When this door closes, it will
not open again.

390
00:30:35,361 --> 00:30:36,601
I should've been with you.

391
00:30:36,901 --> 00:30:38,894
No. Belle, listen to me.

392
00:30:39,418 --> 00:30:40,982
It's all right.

393
00:30:41,261 --> 00:30:42,690
Now, go.

394
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:44,401
Live your life.

395
00:30:44,706 --> 00:30:45,941
And forget me.

396
00:30:46,141 --> 00:30:47,443
Forget you?

397
00:30:47,783 --> 00:30:49,443
Everything I aim is because of you.

398
00:30:50,703 --> 00:30:52,012
I love you, Belle.

399
00:30:52,423 --> 00:30:53,623
Don't be afraid.

400
00:30:54,464 --> 00:30:56,130
I love you too, Papa.

401
00:30:57,023 --> 00:30:58,605
I'm not afraid.

402
00:31:01,508 --> 00:31:02,856
And I will escape, I promise.

403
00:31:04,354 --> 00:31:05,354
Wh.. What?

404
00:31:11,661 --> 00:31:12,822
You took his place.

405
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:14,207
He is my father.

406
00:31:14,624 --> 00:31:16,075
He's a fool.

407
00:31:16,675 --> 00:31:18,211
And so are you.

408
00:31:19,786 --> 00:31:20,786
Belle..

409
00:31:21,976 --> 00:31:22,976
Papa!

410
00:31:23,567 --> 00:31:24,755
Don't hurt him!

411
00:31:24,993 --> 00:31:26,062
- Papa!
- No!

412
00:31:28,528 --> 00:31:29,537
I'll come back!

413
00:31:30,394 --> 00:31:31,529
I promise!

414
00:31:43,869 --> 00:31:45,930
Forgive my intrusion, mademoiselle.

415
00:31:46,196 --> 00:31:48,930
But I have come to escort you
to your room.

416
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,929
My room?

417
00:31:51,905 --> 00:31:53,150
- But I thought...
- Oh, what?

418
00:31:53,415 --> 00:31:56,962
That "Once this door closes,
it will not open again"?

419
00:31:58,115 --> 00:31:59,115
I know.

420
00:31:59,232 --> 00:32:00,232
He gets all dramatic.

421
00:32:00,653 --> 00:32:01,653
Hallo!

422
00:32:06,488 --> 00:32:07,688
Oh, you are very strong.

423
00:32:08,053 --> 00:32:09,455
This is a great quality.

424
00:32:10,107 --> 00:32:11,232
What are you?

425
00:32:11,908 --> 00:32:13,008
I am Lumière!

426
00:32:13,589 --> 00:32:15,491
And.. You can talk?

427
00:32:15,843 --> 00:32:17,804
Of course, he can talk.

428
00:32:18,413 --> 00:32:20,077
It's all he ever does.

429
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:22,985
Now, Lumière, as the head of
the household,

430
00:32:23,425 --> 00:32:25,265
I demand that you to put her
back in her cell at once.

431
00:32:25,364 --> 00:32:27,162
What do you want to be
for the rest of your life, Cogsworth?

432
00:32:27,571 --> 00:32:29,160
A man or a mental clock?

433
00:32:30,170 --> 00:32:31,256
Ready, miss?

434
00:32:31,635 --> 00:32:32,635
Trust me.

435
00:32:35,483 --> 00:32:38,987
You must forgive first impressions.
I hope you are not too startled.

436
00:32:39,375 --> 00:32:40,899
Why would I be startled?

437
00:32:41,197 --> 00:32:42,317
I'm talking to a candle.

438
00:32:42,342 --> 00:32:43,837
Candelabro, please.

439
00:32:44,192 --> 00:32:45,192
You know there's a difference.

440
00:32:45,589 --> 00:32:47,781
But consider me at your service.
The castle is your own now,

441
00:32:48,088 --> 00:32:49,928
so feel free to go anywhere
you like.

442
00:32:50,369 --> 00:32:51,714
Except the west wing.

443
00:32:53,623 --> 00:32:55,197
Uh, which we do not have.

444
00:32:55,609 --> 00:32:57,840
Why? What's in the west wing?

445
00:32:58,095 --> 00:32:59,095
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

446
00:32:59,276 --> 00:33:00,396
- Storage space.
- Storage space.

447
00:33:00,640 --> 00:33:01,640
- That's it
- That's it.

448
00:33:01,759 --> 00:33:02,759
Yes, that's it!

449
00:33:02,838 --> 00:33:04,195
This way, please.
To the east wing.

450
00:33:04,575 --> 00:33:07,142
As I like to call it,
it's the only wing.

451
00:33:08,490 --> 00:33:10,443
Ha ha. Watch your step,
s'il vou plait!

452
00:33:19,477 --> 00:33:21,260
Welcome to your new room!

453
00:33:21,563 --> 00:33:23,380
It's modest, but comortable.

454
00:33:39,844 --> 00:33:41,432
It's.. beautiful.

455
00:33:41,798 --> 00:33:42,798
But of course,

456
00:33:43,085 --> 00:33:45,462
The Master wanted you to have
the finest room in the castle.

457
00:33:47,409 --> 00:33:49,347
Oh, dear. We were not expecting guest.

458
00:33:50,247 --> 00:33:52,300
Enchanté, mademoiselle.

459
00:33:52,936 --> 00:33:53,936
Don't worry.

460
00:33:54,168 --> 00:33:57,061
I'll have this place spotless
in no time.

461
00:34:00,305 --> 00:34:02,325
This plan of yours is
dangerous.

462
00:34:02,684 --> 00:34:05,391
I would've risk anything to kiss you
again, Plumette.

463
00:34:05,723 --> 00:34:08,263
No, my love. I've been burnt
by you before.

464
00:34:08,537 --> 00:34:09,537
We must be strong.

465
00:34:09,615 --> 00:34:11,849
How can I be strong when
you make me so..

466
00:34:17,951 --> 00:34:19,523
Is everything here alive?

467
00:34:20,175 --> 00:34:21,846
Hello. What's your name?

468
00:34:24,336 --> 00:34:25,900
That is a hairbrush.

469
00:34:30,373 --> 00:34:31,678
Do not be alarmed.

470
00:34:32,017 --> 00:34:33,192
This is just your wardrobe.

471
00:34:33,462 --> 00:34:36,667
Meet Madame De Garderobe.
A great singer.

472
00:34:36,993 --> 00:34:38,353
Which you can stay awake.

473
00:34:38,652 --> 00:34:42,153
Cogsworth! A diva needs
a beauty rest.

474
00:34:43,555 --> 00:34:45,322
Stay with us, Madame.

475
00:34:45,582 --> 00:34:47,112
We have someone for you
to dress!

476
00:34:48,485 --> 00:34:49,513
Ah, finally!

477
00:34:49,702 --> 00:34:51,507
A woman!

478
00:34:51,809 --> 00:34:53,604
Pretty eyes.

479
00:34:53,870 --> 00:34:54,870
Proud face.

480
00:34:54,974 --> 00:34:56,654
A perfect canvas. Yes!

481
00:34:57,254 --> 00:35:00,034
I will find you something worthy
of a princess.

482
00:35:00,377 --> 00:35:01,429
I'm not a princess.

483
00:35:01,742 --> 00:35:02,742
Non sense!

484
00:35:02,896 --> 00:35:05,447
Let's see what I got
in my drawer.

485
00:35:07,142 --> 00:35:08,796
Oh! How embarassing!

486
00:35:10,077 --> 00:35:11,726
<i>Froufrou, come and help mama.</i>

487
00:35:22,426 --> 00:35:24,026
Perfecto!

488
00:35:25,088 --> 00:35:27,406
Subtle, understated. I love it!
Au revoir!

489
00:35:28,594 --> 00:35:31,733
<i>Froufrou, send my love to
the maestro.</i>

490
00:36:06,739 --> 00:36:07,739
Picture it, LeFou.

491
00:36:07,964 --> 00:36:09,264
A rustic cabin,

492
00:36:09,564 --> 00:36:11,846
My latest kill roasting on the fire.

493
00:36:12,266 --> 00:36:14,972
Adorable children running around us,
while my love...

494
00:36:15,586 --> 00:36:17,197
rubs my tired feet.

495
00:36:17,467 --> 00:36:19,113
But what did Belle say?

496
00:36:19,587 --> 00:36:21,747
"I will never marry you, Gaston!"

497
00:36:22,231 --> 00:36:24,589
You know, there are other girls.

498
00:36:26,133 --> 00:36:28,677
A great man doesn't waste
his time.

499
00:36:29,271 --> 00:36:31,603
<i>Gosh, it disturbs me to see you, Gaston</i>

500
00:36:31,909 --> 00:36:33,693
<i>Looking so down in the dumps.</i>

501
00:36:35,209 --> 00:36:38,182
<i>Every guy here'd love to be you, Gaston.</i>

502
00:36:38,428 --> 00:36:40,947
<i>Even when taking your lumps.</i>

503
00:36:41,309 --> 00:36:44,130
<i>There's no men in town as admired
as you.</i>

504
00:36:44,469 --> 00:36:47,175
<i>You're everyone's favorite guy</i>

505
00:36:48,128 --> 00:36:51,807
<i>Everyone's awed and inspired by you</i>

506
00:36:52,016 --> 00:36:57,516
<i>And it's not very hard
to see why</i>

507
00:36:59,707 --> 00:37:03,252
<i>No one's slick as Gaston</i>

508
00:37:03,593 --> 00:37:05,234
<i>No one's quick as Gaston</i>

509
00:37:05,512 --> 00:37:08,933
<i>No one's neck's as incredibly thick as Gaston's</i>

510
00:37:09,193 --> 00:37:12,163
<i>For there's no man in town half as manly</i>

511
00:37:12,627 --> 00:37:15,543
<i>Perfect, a pure paragon!</i>

512
00:37:15,904 --> 00:37:18,827
<i>You can ask any Tom, Dick, or Stanley</i>

513
00:37:19,049 --> 00:37:23,876
<i>And they'll tell you whose team they prefer to be on</i>

514
00:37:24,235 --> 00:37:29,120
<i>Who plays...?</i>

