01:13:46,981 --> 01:13:49,719
<i>And who'd have guessed they'd come
together on their own?</i>

1011
01:13:49,921 --> 01:13:51,622
<i>It's so peculiar, wait and see</i>

1012
01:13:51,923 --> 01:13:54,502
<i>We'll wait and see
A few days more</i>

1013
01:13:54,803 --> 01:13:57,844
<i>There may be something there
that wasn't there before</i>

1014
01:13:58,602 --> 01:14:00,293
Well, here's a thought..

1015
01:14:00,594 --> 01:14:04,202
Perhaps there's something there
that wasn't there before

1016
01:14:04,814 --> 01:14:06,009
What, Mama?

1017
01:14:07,210 --> 01:14:12,973
<i>There may be something there
that wasn't there before</i>

1018
01:14:14,429 --> 01:14:16,832
What is it? What's there?

1019
01:14:17,032 --> 01:14:19,528
I will tell you when you're older.

1020
01:14:20,460 --> 01:14:22,471
Okay, I'm older.

1021
01:14:23,503 --> 01:14:24,603
Oh, Chip.

1022
01:14:25,608 --> 01:14:27,740
You are ***

1023
01:14:42,318 --> 01:14:43,690
What are you reading?

1024
01:14:43,991 --> 01:14:44,991
Nothing.

1025
01:14:46,306 --> 01:14:47,813
<i>Guinevere and Lancelot</i>

1026
01:14:48,114 --> 01:14:49,677
Well, actually..

1027
01:14:49,878 --> 01:14:52,130
King Arthur and the Round Table,

1028
01:14:52,330 --> 01:14:55,206
Knights, men, swords, and
so on.

1029
01:14:56,899 --> 01:14:58,042
But still

1030
01:14:58,787 --> 01:14:59,787
it's a romance.

1031
01:14:59,934 --> 01:15:01,234
Alright.

1032
01:15:04,811 --> 01:15:07,165
I never thank you for saving
my life.

1033
01:15:08,039 --> 01:15:09,630
Well, I never thank you

1034
01:15:09,931 --> 01:15:12,459
for not leaving me to be eaten
by wolves.

1035
01:15:16,421 --> 01:15:18,209
They know how to have
a good time.

1036
01:15:18,410 --> 01:15:22,350
Yes, but when I enter the room,
the laughter dies.

1037
01:15:23,352 --> 01:15:24,625
Me, too.

1038
01:15:26,798 --> 01:15:28,906
The villagers say that I'm
a funny girl.

1039
01:15:29,107 --> 01:15:31,264
But I'm not sure they mean it
as a compliment.

1040
01:15:31,465 --> 01:15:32,465
I'm sorry.

1041
01:15:33,744 --> 01:15:35,603
Your village sounds terrible.

1042
01:15:36,805 --> 01:15:38,245
Not as lonely as your castle.

1043
01:15:40,338 --> 01:15:42,771
What dou you say
we'd runaway?

1044
01:15:55,113 --> 01:15:58,348
Another little gift from the enchantress.

1045
01:16:01,942 --> 01:16:04,660
A book that'll allow you to escape.

1046
01:16:11,005 --> 01:16:12,005
Amazing!

1047
01:16:13,109 --> 01:16:15,477
It was the cruelest trick of all.

1048
01:16:16,035 --> 01:16:18,125
It was just another curse.

1049
01:16:18,326 --> 01:16:22,505
The outside world has no place
for a creature like me.

1050
01:16:23,283 --> 01:16:25,050
But it can for you.

1051
01:16:30,786 --> 01:16:34,210
Think of the one place you've always
wanted to see.

1052
01:16:37,026 --> 01:16:40,443
Now, find it in your mind's eye.

1053
01:16:41,043 --> 01:16:42,828
And then feel it in your heart.

1054
01:17:13,418 --> 01:17:15,338
Where did you take us?

1055
01:17:15,939 --> 01:17:17,122
Paris.

1056
01:17:17,722 --> 01:17:19,832
I used to love Paris.

1057
01:17:21,796 --> 01:17:23,443
What would you like to see first?

1058
01:17:23,644 --> 01:17:24,702
Notre Dame?

1059
01:17:25,003 --> 01:17:26,705
Los Champs-Élysées?

1060
01:17:27,007 --> 01:17:27,806
No?

1061
01:17:28,007 --> 01:17:29,952
Too touristy?

1062
01:17:31,059 --> 01:17:33,897
It's so much more that I imagined.

1063
01:17:43,373 --> 01:17:47,182
<i>This is the Paris of my childhood</i>

1064
01:17:48,334 --> 01:17:52,391
<i>This what the borders of my life</i>

1065
01:17:52,592 --> 01:17:56,817
<i>In this crumbling dusty attic</i>

1066
01:17:57,118 --> 01:18:01,242
<i>Where an artist loved his wife</i>

1067
01:18:02,147 --> 01:18:06,245
<i>Is it to remember?</i>

1068
01:18:06,546 --> 01:18:10,212
<i>Or it to move on?</i>

1069
01:18:13,378 --> 01:18:16,534
<i>Knowing the Paris of my childhood..</i>

1070
01:18:18,435 --> 01:18:20,688
<i>is gone</i>

1071
01:18:28,138 --> 01:18:29,416
What happened to your mother?

1072
01:18:29,618 --> 01:18:32,719
It was the one story, Papa can never
bring himself to tell.

1073
01:18:33,019 --> 01:18:34,706
I think, better not to ask.

1074
01:18:37,742 --> 01:18:39,364
A doctor's mask.

1075
01:18:47,655 --> 01:18:48,969
Plague.

1076
01:18:54,620 --> 01:18:56,444
You must leave. Now.

1077
01:19:00,741 --> 01:19:01,529
<i>Quickly...</i>

1078
01:19:01,730 --> 01:19:03,229
before it takes her, too.

1079
01:19:21,338 --> 01:19:24,398
I'm sorry I ever called your father
a thief.

1080
01:19:27,090 --> 01:19:28,502
Let's go home.

1081
01:19:35,161 --> 01:19:36,850
It's just some storm, huh?

1082
01:19:37,051 --> 01:19:40,669
At least, we're not tied to a tree
in the middle of nowhere,

1083
01:19:40,970 --> 01:19:42,784
surrounded by bloodthirsts
and wolves.

1084
01:19:43,185 --> 01:19:44,634
You know, it's not too late.

1085
01:19:44,835 --> 01:19:46,267
We could always turn back..

1086
01:19:48,718 --> 01:19:49,718
It's just..

1087
01:19:49,819 --> 01:19:51,933
everytime I close my eyes,

1088
01:19:52,133 --> 01:19:53,718
I picture Maurice stranded alone.

1089
01:19:53,919 --> 01:19:55,215
And when I open them,

1090
01:19:56,049 --> 01:19:57,086
he is..

1091
01:19:58,722 --> 01:20:00,391
Maurice?

1092
01:20:02,720 --> 01:20:04,052
Gaston,

1093
01:20:04,254 --> 01:20:06,413
did you try to kill Maurice?

1094
01:20:09,808 --> 01:20:11,284
Maurice!

1095
01:20:11,484 --> 01:20:12,886
Thank heavens!

1096
01:20:13,505 --> 01:20:15,568
I've spent the last five days

1097
01:20:15,770 --> 01:20:16,850
trying to find you!

1098
01:20:16,898 --> 01:20:17,898
You tried to kill me.

1099
01:20:17,998 --> 01:20:19,643
You left me to the wolves.

1100
01:20:19,944 --> 01:20:21,043
Wolves?

1101
01:20:21,344 --> 01:20:23,808
It's one thing to rave about
your delusions

1102
01:20:24,010 --> 01:20:26,297
and another, to accuse me of
attempted murder.

1103
01:20:26,767 --> 01:20:27,767
Maurice,

1104
01:20:28,142 --> 01:20:30,805
do you have any proof of
what you're saying?

1105
01:20:33,350 --> 01:20:35,298
Ask Agathe. She rescued me.

1106
01:20:35,599 --> 01:20:37,012
Agathe!

1107
01:20:38,710 --> 01:20:40,829
You'd hang your accusations
on the testimony

1108
01:20:41,031 --> 01:20:42,579
of a filthy hag?

1109
01:20:42,780 --> 01:20:44,573
No offense, Agathe.

1110
01:20:47,730 --> 01:20:48,730
Monsieur LeFou.

1111
01:20:49,267 --> 01:20:51,904
He was there. He saw it all.

1112
01:20:52,554 --> 01:20:53,554
Me?

1113
01:20:53,838 --> 01:20:55,279
You're right!

1114
01:20:55,479 --> 01:20:57,110
Don't take my word for it.

1115
01:20:57,711 --> 01:20:58,711
LeFou!

1116
01:21:00,012 --> 01:21:01,780
My dearest companion.

1117
01:21:01,981 --> 01:21:02,982
Did I,

1118
01:21:03,383 --> 01:21:06,382
your loyal friend and most loyal
compatriot,

1119
01:21:06,583 --> 01:21:10,405
try to kill the father of the only woman
I've ever loved?

1120
01:21:10,606 --> 01:21:13,871
Well, it's a complicated question on a
number of accounts.

1121
01:21:15,857 --> 01:21:17,291
But, no.

1122
01:21:18,493 --> 01:21:19,587
No, he did not.

1123
01:21:20,970 --> 01:21:21,980
You!

1124
01:21:29,249 --> 01:21:30,560
Maurice,

1125
01:21:31,557 --> 01:21:35,651
it pains me to say this, but you've become
a danger to yourself and others.

1126
01:21:35,852 --> 01:21:38,745
No wonder, Belle runaway.

1127
01:21:38,946 --> 01:21:40,508
You need a help, Sir.

1128
01:21:40,710 --> 01:21:43,170
A place to heal your
troubled mind.

1129
01:21:46,050 --> 01:21:48,248
Everything is gonna be fine.

1130
01:21:48,749 --> 01:21:49,749
Just fine.

1131
01:21:53,468 --> 01:21:54,628
Well, I'd saw her in the ballroom,

1132
01:21:54,763 --> 01:21:56,750
and said, "You're making everything
looks so beautiful,

1133
01:21:56,952 --> 01:22:00,697
we should have a dance tonight".
I never imagined she'd actually say yes.

1134
01:22:00,899 --> 01:22:01,899
What was I thinking?

1135
01:22:02,149 --> 01:22:04,612
No, Master. It's perfect!

1136
01:22:04,813 --> 01:22:07,255
The rose has only four petals left,
which means tonight..

1137
01:22:07,556 --> 01:22:09,378
You can tell her how you feel.

1138
01:22:10,080 --> 01:22:11,362
I feel like a fool.

1139
01:22:12,443 --> 01:22:14,014
She will never love me.

1140
01:22:14,215 --> 01:22:15,358
Do not be discourage.

1141
01:22:16,981 --> 01:22:18,388
She is the one.

1142
01:22:18,632 --> 01:22:20,657
Please, stop saying that!

1143
01:22:22,266 --> 01:22:23,735
There is no "one".

1144
01:22:23,936 --> 01:22:25,313
You care for her, don't you?

1145
01:22:25,514 --> 01:22:29,913
Well then, woo her with beautiful music
and romantic candlelight.

1146
01:22:30,013 --> 01:22:33,061
Yes, and when the moments just right.
Hmhhm.

1147
01:22:33,647 --> 01:22:34,995
Well, how will I know?

1148
01:22:35,096 --> 01:22:36,539
You'll feel slightly nauseous.

1149
01:22:36,740 --> 01:22:39,028
Don't worry, Master. You'll do fine.

1150
01:22:39,229 --> 01:22:43,616
Just don't be so nervous and
tell Belle how you feel.

1151
01:22:43,817 --> 01:22:45,018
Because if you dont,

1152
01:22:45,218 --> 01:22:48,065
I promise, you'll be drinking cold tea
for the rest of your days!

1153
01:22:48,266 --> 01:22:49,866
- In the dark.
- Covered in dust.

1154
01:22:50,068 --> 01:22:52,440
Dark and very, very dirty.

1155
01:22:53,567 --> 01:22:54,669
Start with the hair.

1156
01:22:54,870 --> 01:22:56,350
Women love nice hair!

1157
01:22:56,679 --> 01:22:58,031
How tidy the fingers and toes?

1158
01:22:58,055 --> 01:23:01,204
Chapeau, brush those teeth.
They need it.

1159
01:23:01,405 --> 01:23:02,406
Deep, deep.

1160
01:23:02,608 --> 01:23:04,597
Snip, snip.

1161
01:23:05,585 --> 01:23:07,042
Polish the nails.

1162
01:23:07,343 --> 01:23:08,880
Shine the horn.

1163
01:23:09,081 --> 01:23:10,481
Eyes close. Puff, puff.

1164
01:23:10,725 --> 01:23:12,329
And to top final look.

1165
01:23:13,945 --> 01:23:15,281
Voilà!

1166
01:23:16,689 --> 01:23:19,374
Okay, I can fix this.

1167
01:23:28,715 --> 01:23:30,335
Oh, beautiful!

1168
01:23:30,581 --> 01:23:31,935
But something has missing.

1169
01:23:32,884 --> 01:23:34,959
Oh, yes!

1170
01:23:36,070 --> 01:23:38,969
The finishing touch!

1171
01:24:43,926 --> 01:24:47,665
<i>Tale as old as time</i>

1172
01:24:49,234 --> 01:24:52,892
<i>True as it can be</i>

1173
01:24:54,879 --> 01:24:57,454
<i>Barely even friends</i>

1174
01:24:57,755 --> 01:25:02,317
<i>Then somebody bends
unexpectedly</i>

1175
01:25:05,640 --> 01:25:08,786
<i>Just a little change</i>

1176
01:25:10,691 --> 01:25:13,068
<i>Small, to say the least</i>

1177
01:25:13,788 --> 01:25:16,391
<i>Both a little scared</i>

1178
01:25:16,593 --> 01:25:18,551
<i>Neither one prepared</i>

1179
01:25:19,741 --> 01:25:23,890
<i>Beauty and the Beast</i>

1180
01:25:34,751 --> 01:25:37,345
<i>Ever just the same</i>

1181
01:25:41,327 --> 01:25:45,677
<i>Ever a surprise</i>

1182
01:25:48,430 --> 01:25:50,881
<i>Ever as before</i>

1183
01:25:51,082 --> 01:25:54,198
<i>Ever just as sure</i>

1184
01:25:54,400 --> 01:25:59,353
<i>As the sun will rise</i>

1185
01:26:01,388 --> 01:26:04,977
<i>Tale as old as time</i>

1186
01:26:07,694 --> 01:26:11,741
<i>Tune as old as song</i>

1187
01:26:14,186 --> 01:26:16,573
<i>Bittersweet and strange</i>

1188
01:26:16,773 --> 01:26:19,532
<i>Finding you can change</i>

1189
01:26:19,834 --> 01:26:23,227
<i>Learning you were wrong</i>

1190
01:26:36,156 --> 01:26:39,923
<i>Certain as the sun</i>

1191
01:26:42,609 --> 01:26:45,428
<i>Rising in the east</i>

1192
01:26:45,629 --> 01:26:48,349
<i>Tale as old as time</i>

1193
01:26:48,650 --> 01:26:51,887
<i>Song as old as rhyme</i>

1194
01:26:52,188 --> 01:26:56,672
<i>Beauty and the beast.</i>

1195
01:26:58,569 --> 01:27:01,921
<i>Tale as old as time</i>

1196
01:27:02,121 --> 01:27:05,165
<i>Song as old as rhyme</i>

1197
01:27:06,663 --> 01:27:12,531
<i>Beauty and the beast.</i>

1198
01:27:29,877 --> 01:27:31,897
I hadn't dance in years.

1199
01:27:33,107 --> 01:27:35,087
I almost forgot how to feel it.

1200
01:27:45,000 --> 01:27:47,145
It's foolish, I suppose,

1201
01:27:48,145 --> 01:27:50,833
for a creature like me, to hope..

1202
01:27:51,033 --> 01:27:53,861
that one day he might earn
your affection.

1203
01:27:55,223 --> 01:27:56,554
I don't know.

1204
01:27:56,755 --> 01:27:58,152
Really?

1205
01:27:59,514 --> 01:28:01,371
You think you could be happy here?

1206
01:28:06,744 --> 01:28:09,442
Can anybody be happy
if they're free?

1207
01:28:19,577 --> 01:28:21,052
My father taught me to dance.

1208
01:28:22,901 --> 01:28:24,484
I used to step on his toes
a lot.

1209
01:28:28,093 --> 01:28:30,139
You must miss him.

1210
01:28:32,627 --> 01:28:33,678
Very much.

1211
01:28:40,773 --> 01:28:42,593
Would you like to see him?

1212
01:28:51,363 --> 01:28:53,383
I'd like to see my father.

1213
01:28:56,980 --> 01:28:58,082
Papa!

1214
01:28:59,865 --> 01:29:01,611
What are they doing to him?

1215
01:29:01,812 --> 01:29:03,351
He.. He's in trouble!

1216
01:29:04,699 --> 01:29:05,983
Then you must go to him.

1217
01:29:08,668 --> 01:29:09,668
What did you say?

1218
01:29:11,139 --> 01:29:13,048
You must go to him.

1219
01:29:14,910 --> 01:29:16,147
No time to waste.

1220
01:29:21,799 --> 01:29:22,613
No.

1221
01:29:22,814 --> 01:29:24,313
You keep it with you.

1222
01:29:26,463 --> 01:29:29,151
And you'll always have a way
to look back on me.

1223
01:29:34,820 --> 01:29:36,108
Thank you.

1224
01:30:21,729 --> 01:30:24,290
Well, Master, I have had my doubts,
but everything's moving like clockwork.

1225
01:30:24,892 --> 01:30:27,435
True love really does win the day!

1226
01:30:30,318 --> 01:30:31,738
I let her go.

1227
01:30:32,039 --> 01:30:33,629
What?

1228
01:30:33,930 --> 01:30:35,645
Master, how could you do that?

1229
01:30:35,845 --> 01:30:37,752
I had to.

1230
01:30:38,353 --> 01:30:39,353
But, why?

1231
01:30:39,529 --> 01:30:41,394
Because, he loves her.

1232
01:30:41,996 --> 01:30:43,483
Then, why are we not human?

1233
01:30:43,683 --> 01:30:47,115
Because, she doesn't love him.
And now, it's too late.

1234
01:30:47,315 --> 01:30:49,111
But she might still come back.

1235
01:30:49,412 --> 01:30:50,946
No.

1236
01:30:51,547 --> 01:30:52,845
I set her free.

1237
01:30:54,420 --> 01:30:57,270
I'm sorry I couldn't do the same
for all of you.

1238
01:30:57,571 --> 01:30:59,050
Now, go.

1239
01:30:59,251 --> 01:31:01,386
Our time has so much passed.

1240
01:31:05,978 --> 01:31:07,242
Go, my love.

1241
01:31:10,321 --> 01:31:13,544
<i>I was the one who had it all</i>

1242
01:31:15,084 --> 01:31:17,982
<i>I was the master of my fate</i>

1243
01:31:19,865 --> 01:31:24,286
<i>I never needed anybody in my life</i>

1244
01:31:24,587 --> 01:31:28,202
<i>I learnt the truth too late</i>

1245
01:31:29,312 --> 01:31:32,621
<i>I'll never shake away the pain</i>

1246
01:31:33,819 --> 01:31:37,490
<i>I close my eyes but
she's still there</i>

1247
01:31:38,577 --> 01:31:42,839
<i>I let her steal into my melancholy heart</i>

1248
01:31:43,540 --> 01:31:46,710
<i>It's more than I can bear</i>

1249
01:31:49,834 --> 01:31:54,900
<i>Now I know she'll never leave me</i>

1250
01:31:55,201 --> 01:31:59,600
<i>Even as she runs away</i>

1251
01:31:59,880 --> 01:32:04,383
<i>She will still torment me
Calm me, hurt me</i>

1252
01:32:04,585 --> 01:32:07,820
<i>Move me, come what may</i>

1253
01:32:09,769 --> 01:32:13,419
<i>Wasting in my lonely tower</i>

1254
01:32:13,620 --> 01:32:17,528
<i>Waiting by an open door</i>

1255
01:32:18,965 --> 01:32:22,160
<i>I'll fool myself, she'll walk right in</i>

1256
01:32:24,065 --> 01:32:28,195
<i>And be with me forevermore</i>

1257
01:32:30,993 --> 01:32:34,159
<i>I rage against the trials of love</i>

1258
01:32:35,679 --> 01:32:38,130
<i>I curse the fading of the light</i>

1259
01:32:40,049 --> 01:32:43,733
<i>Though she's already flown so far
beyond my reach</i>

1260
01:32:44,573 --> 01:32:50,485
<i>She's never out of sight</i>

1261
01:32:50,686 --> 01:32:54,997
<i>Now I know she'll never leave me</i>

1262
01:32:55,998 --> 01:33:00,645
<i>Even as she fades from view</i>

1263
01:33:00,846 --> 01:33:02,694
<i>She will still inspire me</i>

1264
01:33:02,894 --> 01:33:08,419
<i>Be a part of everything I do</i>

1265
01:33:09,477 --> 01:33:13,401
<i>Wasting in my lonely tower</i>

1266
01:33:14,261 --> 01:33:17,441
<i>Waiting by an open door</i>

1267
01:33:19,001 --> 01:33:22,149
<i>I'll fool myself, she'll walk right in</i>

1268
01:33:23,351 --> 01:33:26,358
<i>And as the long, long nights begin</i>

1269
01:33:27,741 --> 01:33:30,922
<i>I'll think of all that might have been</i>

1270
01:33:31,896 --> 01:33:38,737
<i>Waiting here forevermore</i>

1271
01:34:00,456 --> 01:34:01,456
This man is weak, please!

1272
01:34:01,858 --> 01:34:03,337
He needs a hospital.

1273
01:34:03,839 --> 01:34:04,839
Not an assylum!

1274
01:34:08,151 --> 01:34:11,167
Have you ever see the inside
of a mad house, Maurice?

1275
01:34:11,562 --> 01:34:13,102
You wouldn't last a week.

1276
01:34:13,304 --> 01:34:15,399
Just give me your daughter's hands,
and I'll set you free.

1277
01:34:15,799 --> 01:34:16,799
Never.

1278
01:34:20,020 --> 01:34:21,348
Take him away!

1279
01:34:29,755 --> 01:34:30,755
Stop!

1280
01:34:43,428 --> 01:34:44,428
Papa!

1281
01:34:44,470 --> 01:34:46,074
Ah, Belle. I thought I'd lost you.

1282
01:34:46,274 --> 01:34:48,339
Let him out! He's hurt!

1283
01:34:48,541 --> 01:34:51,246
We can't do that, Miss.
We will take good care of him.

1284
01:34:51,647 --> 01:34:53,362
My father's not crazy!

1285
01:34:53,562 --> 01:34:55,047
Gaston, tell him!

1286
01:34:55,248 --> 01:34:56,932
You know how loyal I am
to your family,

1287
01:34:57,133 --> 01:34:59,873
but your father's been making
some unbelievable claims.

1288
01:35:00,174 --> 01:35:01,742
It's true, Belle.

1289
01:35:01,943 --> 01:35:04,035
He's been raging about a beast

1290
01:35:04,236 --> 01:35:05,289
in a castle!

1291
01:35:05,488 --> 01:35:08,125
I've just come from the castle
and there is a beast!

1292
01:35:08,327 --> 01:35:11,296
You'd say anything to set him free.
Your word is hardly prove!

1293
01:35:11,597 --> 01:35:13,130
You want a proof?

1294
01:35:15,012 --> 01:35:16,774
Show me the Beast!

1295
01:35:26,568 --> 01:35:27,856
That's your proof!

1296
01:35:29,386 --> 01:35:30,490
This is sorcery!

1297
01:35:33,114 --> 01:35:35,385
Look at this beast!

1298
01:35:35,587 --> 01:35:36,922
Look at his face!

1299
01:35:37,924 --> 01:35:39,235
His claws!

1300
01:35:39,536 --> 01:35:41,768
No, no, don't be afraid!

1301
01:35:42,085 --> 01:35:45,188
He's gentle and kind.

1302
01:35:46,176 --> 01:35:48,954
The monster has her under a spell!

1303
01:35:49,232 --> 01:35:53,024
If I didn't know better, I'd say
she even cared for him!

1304
01:35:53,325 --> 01:35:55,381
He's not a monster, Gaston!

1305
01:35:55,481 --> 01:35:56,481
You are!

1306
01:35:58,329 --> 01:35:59,811
The Beast wouldn't hurt anyone.

1307
01:36:00,112 --> 01:36:01,903
I've heard the effect of
dark magic,

1308
01:36:02,003 --> 01:36:04,849
but I've never before see it with
my own eyes!

1309
01:36:05,050 --> 01:36:06,050
This is a threat

1310
01:36:06,164 --> 01:36:07,463
to our very existence!

1311
01:36:09,012 --> 01:36:10,012
We can't have her running out

1312
01:36:10,083 --> 01:36:11,523
to warn the Beast.

1313
01:36:11,631 --> 01:36:12,711
Lock her up, too.

1314
01:36:12,850 --> 01:36:14,168
- No!
- Lock her away!

1315
01:36:14,569 --> 01:36:15,598
- No!
- Shut up!

1316
01:36:15,900 --> 01:36:17,020
You won't get away with this, Gaston!

1317
01:36:17,673 --> 01:36:18,935
Oh, Belle.

1318
01:36:20,588 --> 01:36:22,558
Gaston, with all due respect..

1319
01:36:22,759 --> 01:36:24,219
Do you want to be next?

1320
01:36:25,420 --> 01:36:26,624
Fetch my horse.

1321
01:36:26,826 --> 01:36:28,041
Stand guard!

1322
01:36:28,241 --> 01:36:29,297
Don't let them escape!

1323
01:36:29,498 --> 01:36:31,992
This creature will curse us all
if we don't stop him!

1324
01:36:33,827 --> 01:36:36,299
What I say, we kill the beast!

1325
01:36:36,499 --> 01:36:37,574
Kill the beast!

1326
01:36:40,315 --> 01:36:41,705
<i>We're not safe until he's dead</i>

1327
01:36:41,905 --> 01:36:43,500
<i>He'll come stalking us at night</i>

1328
01:36:43,701 --> 01:36:46,748
<i>Set to sacrifice our children to his
monstrous appetite</i>

1329
01:36:47,048 --> 01:36:50,181
<i>He'll wreak havoc on our village
if we let him wander free</i>

1330
01:36:50,382 --> 01:36:53,739
<i>So it's time to take some action, boys</i>

1331
01:36:53,940 --> 01:36:59,158
<i>It's time to follow me</i>

1332
01:37:00,906 --> 01:37:03,252
<i>Through the mist, through the woods
Through the darkness and the shadows</i>

1333
01:37:03,453 --> 01:37:06,717
<i>It's a nightmare but it's one exciting ride</i>

1334
01:37:06,919 --> 01:37:10,527
<i>Say a prayer, then we're there
At the drawbridge of a castle</i>

1335
01:37:10,729 --> 01:37:14,105
<i>And there's something truly terrible inside</i>

1336
01:37:14,207 --> 01:37:16,897
<i>It's a beast, he's got fangs
Razor sharp ones</i>

1337
01:37:16,998 --> 01:37:19,999
<i>Massive paws, killer claws for the feast</i>

1338
01:37:20,399 --> 01:37:21,746
<i>Hear him roar, see him roam</i>

1339
01:37:22,047 --> 01:37:25,424
<i>But we're not coming home
'Til he's dead</i>

1340
01:37:25,625 --> 01:37:26,724
<i>Good and dead!</i>

1341
01:37:27,225 --> 01:37:28,225
<i>Kill the beast!</i>

1342
01:37:30,686 --> 01:37:32,084
<i>Light your torch, mount your horse</i>

1343
01:37:32,285 --> 01:37:34,032
<i>Screw your courage to the sticking place</i>

1344
01:37:34,234 --> 01:37:37,134
<i>We're counting on Gaston to lead the way</i>

1345
01:37:37,435 --> 01:37:40,535
<i>Call it war, call it threat
You can bet they all will follow</i>

1346
01:37:40,736 --> 01:37:43,701
<i>For in times like this,
they'll do just as I say</i>

1347
01:37:44,001 --> 01:37:47,224
<i>There's a beast running wild,
there's no question</i>

1348
01:37:47,425 --> 01:37:50,541
<i>But I fear the wrong monster's
released</i>

1349
01:37:50,643 --> 01:37:53,876
<i>Sally forth! Tally ho!
Grab your sword! Grab your bow!</i>

1350
01:37:54,177 --> 01:37:58,440
<i>Praise the Lord and here we go!</i>

1351
01:38:01,858 --> 01:38:03,322
Show me the castle!

1352
01:38:05,834 --> 01:38:07,538
At least, they've finally learnt to love.

1353
01:38:07,839 --> 01:38:10,665
It'd be better for us,
if she does love him in return.

1354
01:38:10,866 --> 01:38:15,272
No, this is the first time of
at any real hope, she would.

1355
01:38:15,473 --> 01:38:16,880
Did you hear that, Mama?

1356
01:38:17,081 --> 01:38:18,441
Is it her? Is she coming back?

1357
01:38:18,642 --> 01:38:19,842
Could it be?

1358
01:38:20,143 --> 01:38:21,524
I told you!

1359
01:38:21,924 --> 01:38:23,003
Sacré bleu!

1360
01:38:23,403 --> 01:38:24,403
Invaders!

1361
01:38:24,507 --> 01:38:25,805
Rufianes!

1362
01:38:26,005 --> 01:38:27,661
Well, where do you go?

1363
01:38:27,962 --> 01:38:29,816
So much for true love.

1364
01:38:30,018 --> 01:38:31,811
Frame the barricades!

1365
01:38:32,112 --> 01:38:34,609
And oppose!

1366
01:38:34,810 --> 01:38:36,025
Move aside!

1367
01:38:36,227 --> 01:38:39,225
<i>Hearts ablaze, banners high
We go marching into battle</i>

1368
01:38:39,460 --> 01:38:42,255
<i>Unafraid although the danger's just
increased</i>

1369
01:38:44,092 --> 01:38:47,364
<i>Raise the flag, sing the song
Here we come, we're fifty strong</i>

1370
01:38:47,565 --> 01:38:50,103
<i>And fifty Frenchmen can't be wrong</i>

1371
01:38:50,903 --> 01:38:52,148
<i>Let's kill the Beast!</i>

1372
01:38:55,292 --> 01:38:56,569
We need help.

1373
01:39:00,143 --> 01:39:01,385
I have to warn the Beast.

1374
01:39:01,586 --> 01:39:02,586
Warn him?

1375
01:39:02,748 --> 01:39:04,619
How did you get away from him?

1376
01:39:06,115 --> 01:39:07,915
He let me go, Papa.

1377
01:39:08,688 --> 01:39:10,272
He sent me back to you.

1378
01:39:11,083 --> 01:39:12,314
I don't understand.

1379
01:39:18,524 --> 01:39:19,985
Where did you..?

1380
01:39:20,112 --> 01:39:22,333
He took me there.

1381
01:39:25,697 --> 01:39:28,086
I know what happened to mama.

1382
01:39:28,559 --> 01:39:31,979
Then you know why I had to leave her there.

1383
01:39:32,179 --> 01:39:35,324
I had to protect you. I.. I've always
tried to protect my little girl.

1384
01:39:35,524 --> 01:39:36,932
Probably, too much.

1385
01:39:37,863 --> 01:39:39,547
I understand.

1386
01:39:47,523 --> 01:39:48,813
Will you help me now?

1387
01:39:49,015 --> 01:39:50,685
It's dangerous.

1388
01:39:50,886 --> 01:39:52,187
Yes!

1389
01:39:52,788 --> 01:39:54,017
Yes, it is.

1390
01:39:57,616 --> 01:39:59,361
I could try to pick the lock.

1391
01:40:00,306 --> 01:40:01,307
After all,

1392
01:40:01,507 --> 01:40:05,251
it's, it's only gears and springs.

1393
01:40:08,000 --> 01:40:09,630
But I would need

1394
01:40:09,830 --> 01:40:12,413
something long and sharp.

1395
01:40:13,799 --> 01:40:14,799
Like that.

1396
01:40:15,289 --> 01:40:16,289
Perfect.

1397
01:40:20,828 --> 01:40:22,244
Oh, excuse me, Master.

1398
01:40:22,444 --> 01:40:24,081
I'm sorry to disturb you.

1399
01:40:24,282 --> 01:40:25,838
She's not coming back.

1400
01:40:26,818 --> 01:40:27,858
No.

1401
01:40:28,159 --> 01:40:30,016
They're breaking down the doors.

1402
01:40:30,917 --> 01:40:32,615
Doesn't matter now.

1403
01:40:32,816 --> 01:40:35,241
Just let them come.

1404
01:40:35,542 --> 01:40:38,091
<i>Kill the beast!</i>

1405
01:40:38,291 --> 01:40:39,677
This isn't working.

1406
01:40:39,878 --> 01:40:40,994
I know what to do.

1407
01:40:41,194 --> 01:40:45,463
<i>Kill the beast! Kill the beast!
Kill the beast!</i>

1408
01:40:53,194 --> 01:40:55,145
Are you not at least be concerned

1409
01:40:55,346 --> 01:40:57,208
that this castle might be haunted?

1410
01:40:58,706 --> 01:41:01,040
Don't lose your nerve, LeFou.

1411
01:41:01,641 --> 01:41:02,641
Where are we?

1412
01:41:04,018 --> 01:41:08,055
This place seems familiar.

1413
01:41:08,256 --> 01:41:10,163
Like I've been here before.

1414
01:41:13,153 --> 01:41:14,383
Oh, hello there.

1415
01:41:15,033 --> 01:41:16,033
You must be

1416
01:41:16,128 --> 01:41:17,805
the talking teacup.

1417
01:41:18,647 --> 01:41:19,690
And you must be

1418
01:41:19,790 --> 01:41:21,048
his grandmother.

1419
01:41:21,726 --> 01:41:23,026
Grandmother?

1420
01:41:23,227 --> 01:41:24,227
Attack!

1421
01:41:25,851 --> 01:41:26,851
Oh, hallo!

1422
01:41:42,068 --> 01:41:43,273
Gaston!

1423
01:41:47,254 --> 01:41:48,293
Gaston!

1424
01:41:48,692 --> 01:41:49,692
Help me.

1425
01:41:49,792 --> 01:41:51,095
Sorry, old friend.

1426
01:41:51,695 --> 01:41:53,307
It's hero time.

1427
01:42:13,581 --> 01:42:14,581
Hello.

1428
01:42:16,692 --> 01:42:17,810
Oh, uh, I believe this is yours.

1429
01:42:24,307 --> 01:42:25,353
She is very headstrong.

1430
01:42:27,453 --> 01:42:28,488
Do you have children?

1431
01:42:32,252 --> 01:42:35,141
No one to protect you now, huh?

1432
01:42:44,089 --> 01:42:46,408
One, two, three, four,

1433
01:42:46,608 --> 01:42:48,655
five, six, seven, eight.

1434
01:42:48,956 --> 01:42:50,156
Good shot, Chip, my boy!

1435
01:42:51,859 --> 01:42:52,859
Ha ha!
Excellent!

1436
01:42:52,906 --> 01:42:54,001
The infantery's arrived!

1437
01:42:55,358 --> 01:42:57,551
Now, go and teach some lessons.
Go!

1438
01:42:58,819 --> 01:43:02,411
Yes, those are called books,
you low-grade musketeers!

1439
01:43:04,999 --> 01:43:06,533
Oh! I'm off.

1440
01:43:13,834 --> 01:43:14,988
Just a clock.

1441
01:43:16,428 --> 01:43:17,428
Ha ha. Come here,

1442
01:43:17,663 --> 01:43:18,863
little boys.

1443
01:43:19,464 --> 01:43:21,461
***

1444
01:43:21,761 --> 01:43:25,111
Yes, pretty little boys. Yes!

1445
01:43:26,665 --> 01:43:28,247
Beautiful!

1446
01:43:28,447 --> 01:43:30,166
Go! Be free!

1447
01:43:30,367 --> 01:43:31,853
Be free! Be free!

1448
01:43:44,925 --> 01:43:46,210
How do you like your tea?

1449
01:43:46,412 --> 01:43:47,412
Hot enough?

1450
01:43:48,633 --> 01:43:49,918
Or boiling?

1451
01:43:51,842 --> 01:43:53,271
Mr. Potts!

1452
01:43:56,226 --> 01:43:57,226
Mama!

1453
01:43:59,559 --> 01:44:00,559
Thank you!

1454
01:44:03,770 --> 01:44:04,921
Take my guts!

1455
01:44:06,183 --> 01:44:07,587
Nicely handled!

1456
01:44:07,787 --> 01:44:09,283
Well, I used to be on Gaston's side,

1457
01:44:09,572 --> 01:44:11,197
but we are so in a bad place
right now.

1458
01:44:11,498 --> 01:44:12,719
You're too good for him,
anyway.

1459
01:44:13,020 --> 01:44:13,721
Yeah.

1460
01:44:13,923 --> 01:44:15,139
Should we get back to it then?

1461
01:44:18,782 --> 01:44:19,995
The sweet of music!

1462
01:44:20,196 --> 01:44:21,196
***

1463
01:44:21,597 --> 01:44:23,104
***

1464
01:44:23,205 --> 01:44:24,205
What?

1465
01:44:24,306 --> 01:44:25,306
Maestro!

1466
01:44:25,406 --> 01:44:26,806
Darling! I've lost!

1467
01:44:27,008 --> 01:44:28,893
I'm coming, my love!

1468
01:44:29,094 --> 01:44:30,794
This is it!

1469
01:44:30,995 --> 01:44:34,162
The fat lady is singing!

1470
01:44:46,297 --> 01:44:47,725
Watch your toes!

1471
01:44:51,533 --> 01:44:53,547
That's it! Go! Go!

1472
01:44:54,147 --> 01:44:55,747
Bon voyage!

1473
01:45:01,030 --> 01:45:02,286
***

1474
01:45:02,487 --> 01:45:04,089
Hands stay out!

1475
01:45:24,383 --> 01:45:25,383
Hello, Beast!

1476
01:45:29,199 --> 01:45:30,686
I'm Gaston.

1477
01:45:31,556 --> 01:45:33,168
Belle sent me.

1478
01:45:35,916 --> 01:45:38,108
Were you in love with her?

1479
01:45:40,187 --> 01:45:42,878
Did you honestly think she'd want you?

1480
01:45:58,578 --> 01:45:59,578
Belle!

1481
01:46:01,225 --> 01:46:02,279
Where is he?

1482
01:46:03,341 --> 01:46:04,755
When we return to the village,

1483
01:46:04,956 --> 01:46:06,619
you will marry me!

1484
01:46:06,821 --> 01:46:08,331
And that beast's head

1485
01:46:08,532 --> 01:46:10,379
- will hang on our wall.
- Never!

1486
01:46:26,441 --> 01:46:28,038
I'm telling you, Beast!

1487
01:46:49,188 --> 01:46:50,188
No!

1488
01:46:50,461 --> 01:46:51,661
Belle?

1489
01:46:56,099 --> 01:46:57,099
Belle!

1490
01:46:58,454 --> 01:46:59,454
You came back!

1491
01:46:59,695 --> 01:47:01,310
I tried to stop them!

1492
01:47:01,511 --> 01:47:02,511
Stay there!

1493
01:47:03,170 --> 01:47:04,170
I'm coming!

1494
01:47:31,310 --> 01:47:32,619
Gaston!

1495
01:47:32,819 --> 01:47:33,919
No!

1496
01:47:47,877 --> 01:47:49,606
Don't let me go.

1497
01:47:50,207 --> 01:47:51,373
Please.

1498
01:47:51,774 --> 01:47:53,181
I'll do anything.

1499
01:47:53,382 --> 01:47:54,783
Don't let me, Beast.

1500
01:48:04,134 --> 01:48:05,688
I am not

1501
01:48:05,890 --> 01:48:07,476
the beast.

1502
01:48:14,110 --> 01:48:15,407
Go!

1503
01:48:16,608 --> 01:48:18,324
Get out!

1504
01:48:19,736 --> 01:48:20,736
Don't!

1505
01:48:20,990 --> 01:48:22,089
It's too far!

1506
01:48:38,359 --> 01:48:39,398
Please!

1507
01:48:42,937 --> 01:48:43,937
Come on.

1508
01:49:13,618 --> 01:49:14,846
You came back.

1509
01:49:16,217 --> 01:49:17,989
Of course, I came back.

1510
01:49:18,192 --> 01:49:19,577
I'll never leave you again.

1511
01:49:20,478 --> 01:49:22,509
I'm afraid it's my turn to leave.

1512
01:49:22,709 --> 01:49:24,110
We're together now.

1513
01:49:24,910 --> 01:49:26,389
It's gonna be fine.

1514
01:49:26,790 --> 01:49:28,947
At least I could see you.

1515
01:49:29,348 --> 01:49:31,298
One last time.

1516
01:49:36,466 --> 01:49:37,805
No!

1517
01:49:38,005 --> 01:49:39,306
Please, no!

1518
01:49:42,595 --> 01:49:44,139
Come back!

1519
01:49:51,562 --> 01:49:53,286
We did it, Plumette!

1520
01:49:53,487 --> 01:49:55,604
Victory is ours!

1521
01:49:56,845 --> 01:49:58,304
Plumette?

1522
01:49:58,984 --> 01:50:00,383
Plumette?

1523
01:50:01,335 --> 01:50:03,706
Oh, my darling, Plumette.

1524
01:50:04,937 --> 01:50:06,191
Oh, no.

1525
01:50:06,854 --> 01:50:09,819
Maestro, you were so brave.

1526
01:50:10,220 --> 01:50:12,677
Goodbye, my love.

1527
01:50:14,277 --> 01:50:15,377
Amore!

1528
01:50:15,577 --> 01:50:18,389
No! Don't leave me!

1529
01:50:37,973 --> 01:50:38,973
Chip!

